06/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- In accordance with a campaign promise by Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu, all members of the cabinet published their asset statements Thursday (5 May).
Tariceanu said the move represents an example of correct and transparent governing.
He called on parliament members and other senior public officials to follow suit and make their holdings public.
According to his own declaration of assets, Tariceanu is one of the wealthiest cabinet members.
